cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper proposes a novel convolution layer for processing 3D point cloud data directly, which is relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) as it can be applied to LiDAR semantic segmentation and object detection. The use of learnable filters also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of semantic segmentation, which falls under natural language processing (cs.CL).
